FT  21 OCT 92 / Second quarter outflow curbed
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   JOHANNESBURG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
South African Finance Minister Derek Keys yesterday said foreign investors
withdrew R2bn (Dollars 715m) in the second quarter of 1992 but the outflow
had since been curbed, Reuter reports from Johannesburg.
