companies to install 4m digital-exchange lines over the next five years.
Each of the companies, with their local partners, would be responsible for
installing an equal number of lines.
Critics said too many companies were involved and problems of equipment
compatibility would arise. But NEC and Ericsson, which have been supplying
digital-exchange lines in Malaysia for some years, have already signed firm
contracts. It is understood the other three groups have been assured they
too will be given contracts, if they meet the compatibility specifications.
