<HEADLINE>
FT  21 OCT 92 / International Company News: Kaiser Aluminum tumbles to
Dollars 3.9m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURIE MORSE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CHICAGO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
KAISER Aluminum, the US mining company suffering from low prices for most of
its products, yesterday reported a sharp decline in earnings for the third
quarter.
The company unveiled net income of Dollars 3.9m, or 6 cents a share, for the
quarter, down from Dollars 23.1m, or 41 cents, last time. Sales were Dollars
458.5m, compared with Dollars 509.7m a year ago.
For the first nine months of the year, Kaiser's earnings were Dollars 24.3m,
or 42 cents, down from Dollars 81.3m, or Dollars 1.56, last year. Nine-month
sales were Dollars 1.4bn, compared with Dollars 1.53bn last year.
'Third-quarter results reflect lower realised prices for the company's
alumina, primary aluminium and fabricated aluminium products,' the company
said. It added that lower prices reflected softened demand, combined with a
cyclical worldwide over-supply of aluminium.
Kaiser shipped 164,700 tonnes of primary and fabricated aluminium in the
third quarter, and 518,500 tonnes in the first nine months, compared with
167,000 tonnes and 492,200 tonnes, respectively, in the same 1991 periods.
Primary aluminium accounted for about 48 per cent of Kaiser's third-quarter
shipments, against 52 per cent in the third quarter of 1991.
Alumina shipments totalled 469,000 tonnes in the third quarter, down from
511,300 tonnes in 1991.
Phelps Dodge, the world's second-largest copper producer, reported
third-quarter earnings above analysts' expectations. Net income jumped to
Dollars 119.9m, or Dollars 1.70 per share, an increase of 83 per cent over
third-quarter 1991 earnings of Dollars 64.7m, or 93 cents.
For the first nine months, the US group recorded net income of Dollars
240.9m, or Dollars 3.42 per share, up from Dollars 197.7m, or Dollars 2.85
per share, last year.
Sales were Dollars 672.1m in the third quarter, and Dollars 1.9bn for the
first nine months, compared with Dollars 617.6m and Dollars 1.8bn,
respectively, for the same periods a year ago. Cash-flow from operating
activities reached Dollars 288.5m in the first nine months of 1992.
Third-quarter results include income of Dollars 36.4m, or 52 cents a share,
from the sale of 20 per cent of the company's interest in a Chilean copper
mine to Sumitomo of Japan.
Phelps Dodge Mining Company reported third-quarter operating earnings of
Dollars 113.6m, compared with Dollars 87.3m a year ago, reflecting a higher
average copper price and lower production costs.
</TEXT>
