FT  21 OCT 92 / International Company News: LSI Logic reverses into loss
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LOUISE KEHOE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LSI LOGIC, the US semiconductor manufacturer, suffered third-quarter losses
after Dollars 102m restructuring charges for the closure of its German
production plant and a refocusing of its product lines.
Net losses for the quarter were Dollars 111m, or Dollars 2.51 per share,
compared with a net profit of Dollars 804,000, or 2 cents a share, in the
third quarter last year.
Excluding the results of the charge, the operating loss in the quarter was
Dollars 3m, compared with an operating profit of Dollars 4m in the third
quarter a year ago. Including the restructuring charge, the operating loss
in the third quarter was Dollars 105m.
Revenues in the third quarter were Dollars 154m, down nearly 11 per cent
from Dollars 172m a year ago.
Last month, LSI Logic announced it would accelerate the phasing out of older
manufacturing capacity in the US and Germany, and emphasise higher
value-added products. including application-specific integrated circuits
(Asic).
The growth in third quarter revenues over the prior second quarter reversed
a string of four consecutive quarterly declines.
The net loss for the nine months was Dollars 117m, or Dollars 2.63 per
share, compared with a net profit of Dollars 7m, or 17 cents a share, in the
same period last year. Revenues were Dollars 456m, down nearly 14.5 per cent
from Dollars 534m a year ago.
