The official pointed to Mr Yeltsin's signing yesterday of a decree creating
one single joint stock company controlling all of the Russian gas industry.
This corporation would, he said, exercise a more direct control over the
various gas enterprises than the present state body, Gasprom.
The official said the signing of the decree, which could not be confirmed by
the president's office last night, ran directly counter to government policy
to break the industry into three or four companies.
The industry, and other sectors of the crucial energy complex, would pass to
the control of industrial managers who would 'exploit the consumers who are
not organised as a political force', he said. 'The President is now open to
proposals of this kind. Sometimes these proposals come with threats to stop
production if they are not carried through.'
</TEXT>
