<TEXT>
Taiwan is the subject of BBC2's foreign affairs series Assignment. Brian
Barron reports from the island which became the home of those Chinese who
opposed Mao Tse Tung and which today boasts the world's largest foreign
reserve. The programme accompanies the first delegation of communist Chinese
journalists to visit Taiwan and also films the greatest collection of
ancient Chinese treasures, taken from the Forbidden City when the
Nationalists under Chaing Kai Shek retreated and now kept in tunnels
underneath Taiwan's capital.
BBC2 also offers Beethoven's Not Dead (9.00), a one-off half-hour comedy
adapted from a show first seen at the 1991 Edinburgh Festival with
classically trained musicians Miles and Millner.
Battlecries, one of the series appearing under the umbrella title 'War And
Peace', provides testimony from three Tornado aircrew shot down in the Gulf
War (9.30 BBC2). ITV screens the second part of its highly professional
documentary series The Kennedys. This episode (10.40) concentrates on John
F, showing the part played by father Joe's money in winning the presidency.
